National Leader of the All Progressives Congress(APC) Asiwaju Bola Tinubu on Saturday morning visited a contestant for the party’s National chairmanship, Senator Sani Musa. Tinubu visited the chairman of the Senate Services Committee in his Maitama, Abuja residence, assuring the latter’s contributions to the party will not go in vain. The former Lagos Governor, a presidential aspirant on the platform of the APC, said the Niger East senator will surely be rewarded for his contributions to the success of the party in 2015.   Police kill two suspected kidnappers, rescue victims in…     Lagos Marine bridge rehabilitation 66% completed — Official     Terrorists will be crushed, Buhari reassures Kaduna…   According to him: “The sacrifices of Distinguished Senator Mohammed Sani Musa for the All Progressives Congress in 2014/2015 will not go in vain, the leadership of the ruling All Progressives Congress are fully aware. He will be rewarded.” - Advertisement - Musa pledged to lead the APC in a new direction for electoral victory if elected.